event_list: The Vice President will depart the Republic of Korea en route to Washington, D.C. This departure from Osan Air Base and arrival at Joint Base Andrews will be pooled press.

The Vice President will visit the Demilitarized Zone and receive a tour and operational briefing at multiple sites. She will also meet with service members. This visit will be covered by an expanded pool.

The Vice President will meet with groundbreaking women leaders from the Republic of Korea to demonstrate the importance of elevating gender equity issues around the world. This meeting will have a pool spray at the top open to pre-credentialed media.

The Vice President will participate in a bilateral meeting with President Yoon Suk-yeol of the Republic of Korea. The Vice President will discuss the strength of the U.S.-ROK Alliance, the growing economic and technology partnership, and a range of regional and global issues. This bilateral meeting will have a pool spray at the top.
The Vice President will arrive at Osan Air Base. This arrival will be open to pre-credentialed media.
The Vice President will depart Tokyo, Japan en route to Seoul, Republic of Korea. This departure from Yokota Air Base will be pooled press.
The Vice President will depart Yokosuka Naval Base en route to Hardy Barracks. This departure will be pooled press.

The Vice President will deliver remarks on the USS Howard. The Vice President will discuss U.S. enduring interests and commitments in the region, our work with allies and partners, and the importance of upholding the international rules-based order. These remarks will be open to pre-credentialed media and livestreamed on whitehouse.gov/live.
The Vice President will meet with service members on board the USS Howard. This meeting will have a pool spray at the top.
The Vice President will board the USS Howard and participate in a tour and briefing. This tour will be pooled press.
The Vice President will arrive at Yokosuka Naval Base. This arrival will be pooled press.

The Vice President will host a roundtable discussion with Japanese business executives from companies in the semiconductor industry for a discussion on the CHIPS and Science Act, supply chain resiliency, and research and development. This roundtable will be covered by pre-credentialed media and livestreamed on whitehouse.gov/live.

The Vice President will hold a bilateral meeting with Prime Minister Anthony Albanese of Australia to discuss developments throughout the Indo-Pacific, including our work through the Quad, and our collective work to address the climate crisis. This bilateral meeting at The Okura Tokyo will have a pool spray at the top.

The Vice President will hold a bilateral meeting with Prime Minister Han Duck-soo of the Republic of Korea. They will discuss her upcoming visit to Seoul and how the U.S.-ROK alliance is a linchpin of security and prosperity in the Indo-Pacific. This bilateral meeting at The Okura Tokyo will have a pool spray at the top.
The Vice President will participate in a dinner hosted by Prime Minister Kishida of Japan. This dinner at the Akasaka Palace will be closed press.
